<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Inducement" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Inducement,</orth> that which moves and determines, motive, impulse: <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.279" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 279</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.169" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 169</bibl>. <emph>with his i.</emph> == impelled, instigated, seduced by him, <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 2, 91</bibl>.
